.TH getbar 1 "@PROJECT_YEAR@" "@PROJECT_VERSION@" "Lenh nguoi dung"
.SH NAME
getbar \- chuoi cot throughput tai HTTP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B getbar
.RI [ tuy-chon ]...
.IR URL
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B getbar
tai
.IR URL
bang HTTP hoac HTTPS GET qua libcurl va ghi chuoi cot ra stdout.
Che do khoi ghi thoi gian nhan tung khoi (micro giay); che do khoang thoi gian
ghi so byte nhan moi khoang.
.PP
Mac dinh ghi toan bo timeline, bao gom ket noi va do tre may chu
(TTFB o che do khoi, cac khoang zero dau o che do khoang thoi gian).
Offset da thuc
.BR \-p
la zero tru khi dat
.B \-d
.PP
Voi
.BR \-d ", thoi gian cho truoc du lieu bi loai khoi chuoi cot, "
.BR \-w ", "
.BR \-c ", va fit da thuc; "
.BR \-p
offset bao cao do tre da loai (giay o che do khoang thoi gian, so khoi dau o che do khoi).
.PP
Ket thuc output nghia la tai xong, cham
.B \-\-window
hoac
.BR \-\-size-max ,
hoac that bai.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-block-size =\fINUM\fR[kmgKMG]
Chia thanh khoi
.IR NUM
byte va ghi thoi gian nhan tung khoi (micro giay).
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interval =\fINUM\fR[um][s]
Ghi byte nhan moi
.IR NUM
micro giay, milli giay hoac giay.
.IR NUM
co the la so thap phan (vd.
.BR 0.1s
hoac
.BR 100.5ms ).
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-size-max =\fINUM\fR[kmgKMG]
Dung sau khi nhan
.IR NUM
byte.
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-window =\fINUM\fR[um][s]
Dung sau gioi han thoi gian. Voi
.BR \-d ,
gioi han chi ap dung sau khi du lieu bat dau den.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-polynomial =\fIORDER\fR
Sau chuoi, in dong fit da thuc:
.IR offset
va he so. Mac dinh offset la zero; voi
.BR \-d ,
offset la do tre truoc du lieu da loai (giay o che do khoang thoi gian, so khoi dau o che do khoi).
Cung duong fit duoc ve tren bieu do
.BR \-\-gnuplot
khi dung tuy chon nay.
.TP
.BR \-g ", " \-\-gnuplot =\fIFILE\fR
Ghi output gnuplot vao
.IR FILE .
Duoi
.RB ( .png ", " .svg ", " .pdf ", " .eps )
duoc render bang gnuplot; khac thi chi luu script (khong can gnuplot).
Voi
.BR \-\-polynomial
, bao gom duong fit.
Doc theme tuy chon tu
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME /getbar/gnuplot.rc
neu co.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Ghi de tep output gnuplot hien co.
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-estimate-bps =\fINUM\fR[um][s]
Sau chuoi, in toc do tai uoc tinh (byte/giay), do tu
.IR NUM
sau khi du lieu bat dau den den het transfer.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-count
Sau chuoi, in mot dong tom tat:
.IR series-count size-bytes duration-usec bytes-per-second .
.IR series-count
la so gia tri cot;
.IR size-bytes
la tong byte nhan;
.IR duration-usec
la thoi gian transfer thuc tu diem do den ket thuc (tu luc ket noi tru khi dat
.B \-d
);
.IR bytes-per-second
la throughput trung binh trong khoang do.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-delay-started
Loai thoi gian cho truoc du lieu khoi chuoi cot va khoi
.BR \-w ", " \-c ", va fit da thuc. "
.BR \-p
offset bao cao do tre da loai.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Khong in chuoi cot.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Ghi chi tiet transfer ra stderr.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
In tro giup va thoat.
.TP
.B \-\-version
In phien ban va thoat.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Do luong co ban
.TP
Khoi 64 KiB:
.B getbar \-b 64k https://example.com/file
.TP
Khoang 100 ms, uoc tinh sau 1 s (an chuoi):
.B getbar \-i 100ms \-e 1s \-q https://example.com/file
.TP
Dong tom tat sau chuoi khoang thoi gian:
.B getbar \-i 100ms \-c https://example.com/file
.br
Output ket thuc bang dong nhu
.IR "20 1048576 1523400 688421"
(so cot, byte, micro giay, B/s).
.TP
In time-to-first-byte (micro giay) tu che do khoi:
.B getbar \-b 64k \-s 256k https://example.com/file | awk '{print $1}'
.SS Kiem soat kich thuoc hoac thoi gian
.TP
Lay mau 10 MiB va in uoc tinh B/s on dinh:
.B getbar \-i 100ms \-s 10M \-e 2s \-q https://mirror.example/file
.TP
Chay toi da 30 s (soak test):
.B getbar \-i 1s \-w 30s \-v https://cdn.example/large.bin
.TP
Dung khi dat truoc 50 MiB hoac 60 s:
.B getbar \-b 1M \-s 50M \-w 60s https://example.com/file
.SS Bieu do va phan tich
.TP
Khoang thap phan, cua so 3 s, verbose, ghi de bieu do:
.B getbar \-vfw3 \-i0.1s \-g /tmp/getbar.png \-f https://example.com/file
.TP
Bieu do khoi voi da thuc bac hai:
.B getbar \-b 64k \-p 2 \-g /tmp/getbar.png https://example.com/file
.TP
Bieu do khoang thoi gian voi da thuc:
.B getbar \-i 100ms \-p 2 \-g chart.png \-f https://example.com/file
.TP
Xuat SVG cho bao cao:
.B getbar \-i 200ms \-p 2 \-g report.svg \-f https://example.com/file
.TP
Luu script gnuplot khong render:
.B getbar \-b 64k \-g /tmp/getbar.gp https://example.com/file
.SS So sanh mirror
.TP
Mot dong B/s uoc tinh moi URL (mau 5 MiB):
.B for url in https://mirror-a.example/file https://mirror-b.example/file; do printf '%s\\t' "$url"; getbar \-i 100ms \-s 5M \-e 1s \-q "$url"; done
.TP
Sap xep mirror theo throughput uoc tinh (\fImirrors.txt\fR mot URL moi dong):
.B while read \-r url; do bps=$(getbar \-i 100ms \-s 5M \-e 1s \-q "$url") || continue; printf '%s\\t%s\\n' "$bps" "$url"; done < mirrors.txt | sort \-nr
.SS Tich hop shell
.TP
Log verbose ra stderr, chuoi ra stdout:
.B getbar \-v \-i 100ms \-s 10M https://example.com/file > series.txt
.TP
Luu chuoi va bieu do trong mot lan chay:
.B getbar \-i 100ms \-s 20M \-g run.png \-f https://example.com/file | tee series.txt
.TP
MiB/s xap xi tu dong uoc tinh:
.B bps=$(getbar \-i 100ms \-s 10M \-e 1s \-q https://example.com/file); awk \-v b="$bps" 'BEGIN { printf "~ %.2f MiB/s\\n", b / 1024 / 1024 }'
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/getbar/gnuplot.rc
Lenh gnuplot tuy chon nap truoc khi ve (mau, font, luoi, v.v.).
.SH AUTHOR
Viet boi @PROJECT_AUTHOR@ <@PROJECT_EMAIL@>.
